back.name: Pullup
back.exerciseDescription:
Position hands with overhand grip in line with your shoulders.

Keep feet together and legs straight.

Keep chest up and shoulders down as you pull up.

back.name: Inverted Row
back.exerciseDescription:
Position hands with overhand grip in line with your shoulders.

Keep feet together and legs straight.

Maintain rigid position by squeezing abs and butt tight.

Keep chest up and shoulders down as you pull up.

back.name: Barbell Bent Row
back.exerciseDescription:
Establish stable base, with feet hip to shoulder width apart.

Hinge hip into a bent position.

Brace core tight.

Keep chest up and shoulders down as you pull the bar towards your sternum.

back.name: Dumbbell Bent Row
back.exerciseDescription:
Establish stable base, with feet hip to shoulder width apart.

Hinge hip into a bent position.

Brace core tight.

Keep chest up and shoulders down as you pull dumbbells towards your armpit.

back.name: Cable Pulldowns
back.exerciseDescription:
Sit with stable base with feet.

Torso should be upright and rigid.

Arms should be completely straight to start.

Keep chest up and shoulders down as you pull cable towards your sternum.

chest.name: Barbell Bench Press
chest.exerciseDescription:
Line up grip directly above your shoulders.

Keep feet planted to the floor.

Brace abs and butt tight.

As you lower the bar to your chest, feel squeeze between your shoulder blades before pushing bar up.

chest.name: Dumbbell Bench Press
chest.exerciseDescription:
Position dumbbells directly above chest, in line with your shoulders.

Keep feet planted to the floor.

Brace abs and butt tight.

As you lower dumbbells just outside your chest, feel squeeze between shoulder blades before pushing them back up.

chest.name: Pushup
chest.exerciseDescription:
Keep hands in line with your shoulders.

Keep abs and butt tight.

As you lower, feel squeeze between your shoulder blades before pushing up.

chest.name: Dumbbell Chest Fly
chest.exerciseDescription:
Hold dumbbells directly over your chest with elbows slightly bent (thumbs facing each other).

Keep feet planted on the floor with abs and butt tight.

Your grip should be tight and arms strong as you lower the dumbbells down separating from each other.

Lower the dumbbells down until they are in line with your shoulders.

quads.name: Barbell Back Squat to a Box

calves.name: Leg Press Single Leg Calf Raise

biceps.name: Dumbbell Curl
biceps.exerciseDescription:
Establish stable base with feet hip to shoulder width apart.

Torso should be upright and rigid with core braced.

Grip should be shouler width apart with arms completely straight, palms facing forward (thumbs out).

Bending at the elbow, curl dumbbells up towards your shoulders while maintaining posture.

biceps.name: Barbell Curl
biceps.exerciseDescription:
Establish stable base with feet hip to shoulder width apart.

Torso should be upright and rigid with core braced.

Grip should be shouler width apart with arms completely straight, palms facing forward (thumbs out).

Bending at the elbow, curl the bar up towards your shoulders while maintaining posture.

biceps.name: Cable Curl
biceps.exerciseDescription:
Establish stable base with feet hip to shoulder width apart.

Torso should be upright and rigid with core braced.

Hold bar attached to a low cable with palms up (thumbs out).

Bending at the elbow, curl the cable bar up towards your shoulders while maintaining posture.

triceps.name: Barbell Skullcrusher
triceps.exerciseDescription:
Use an overhand grip on the bar with hands directly above your shoulders or slightly less (to your comfort).

Position bar slightly angled until directly above forehead with arms completely straight.

Keep feet planted to the floor with abs and butt tight.

Maintain stable base and tight core as you bend at the elbow and lower bar towards forehead.

triceps.name: Dumbbell Skullcrusher
triceps.exerciseDescription:
Hold dumbbells with arms completely straight and palms facing each other.

Position dumbbells slightly angled until directly above forehead.

Keep feet planted to the floor with abs and butt tight.

Maintain stable base and tight core as you bend at the elbow and lower dumbbells towards forehead.

triceps.name: Cable Tricep Pulldown
triceps.exerciseDescription:
Establish stable base with feet hip to shoulder width apart.

Torso should be upright and rigid with core braced.

Hold bar attached to a high cable with palms down and elbows tight to your sides.

Bending at the elbow, push the cable bar down towards your thighs while maintaining posture.

shoulders.name: Dumbbell Overhead Press
shoulders.exerciseDescription:
Establish stable base with feet hip to shoulder width apart.

Torso should be upright and rigid with core braced.

Hold dumbbells just outside your shoulders with your arms bent and palms facing each other.

Press dumbbells straight up directly over shoulders with arms completely straight.

shoulders.name: Dumbbell Front Raise
shoulders.exerciseDescription:
Establish stable base with feet hip to shoulder width apart.

Torso should be upright and rigid with core braced.

Hold dumbbells at arm's length next to your sides with your palms facing each other.

Raise dumbbells straight in front of you until they are parallel to the floor and perpendicular to your torso.

shoulders.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
shoulders.exerciseDescription:
Establish stable base with feet hip to shoulder width apart.

Torso should be upright and rigid with core braced.

Hold dumbbells at arm's length next to your sides with your palms facing forward (thumbs out).

Raise dumbbells straight out to your sides until they are at shoulder level, parallel to the floor.

shoulders.name: Barbell Overhead Press
shoulders.exerciseDescription:
Establish stable base with feet hip to shoulder width apart.

Torso should be upright and rigid with core braced.

Grip should be just outside shoulder distance (to your comfort).

Press bar up directly over shoulders with arms completely straight.

shoulders.name: Inverted Floor Press
shoulders.exerciseDescription:
Start in a pushup position, then rock into a downward dog position.

To assume downward dog, push your hips up towards the ceiling and your head and shoulders towards your toes, then hold.

Your hands should be slightly outside your shoulders (to your comfort).

As you lower your upper body down towards the floor, stay bent at the waist, keep your torso rigid and keep core braced.
